        },
        {
            "paragraph": "Make a map"
        },
        {
            "paragraph": "Next, exhaustively document every possible path a user can take on the platform. It doesn’t matter how — you can use a sketchpad or folder full of screenshots. Pay extra attention to the user behaviors you usually ignore, and to these more oblique paths:"
        },
        {
            "paragraph": "Settings page + advanced settings"
        },
        {
            "paragraph": "About pages"
        },
        {
            "paragraph": "Paths that you take to end up on the platform in the first place (for example, from a Google search)"
        },
        {
            "paragraph": "Behaviors that you might take when first creating an account"
        },
        {
            "paragraph": "Advanced search operators or advanced search pages"
        },
        {
            "paragraph": "External tools for searching the platform"
        },
        {
            "paragraph": "External tools for navigating the platform"
        },
        {
            "paragraph": "Sitemaps"
        },
        {
            "paragraph": "Ways that the platform might be navigated “randomly” (has anyone built a random navigator?)"
        },
        {
            "paragraph": "The urls of the pages you visit (does their structure reveal anything that can open doors to navigating by direct url entry?)"
        },
        {
